Colombia Stocks: Ecopetrol Falls; Fabricato, Rubiales Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-23T16:42:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/colombia-stocks-ecopetrol-falls-fabricato-rubiales-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:43 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.4 percent to 14,075.46, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.5 percent to 1,702.65.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest oil company,
fell 1 percent to 3,900 pesos after guerrillas sabotaged the
company’s pipeline in the municipality of Yondo on May 21. The
company said the pipeline has been repaired.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s largest textile maker,
rose 3.8 percent to 55 pesos. Camilo Reyes, the head of the
Colombian-American chamber of commerce, said he expects U.S.
lawmakers to pass a free trade accord with Colombia by mid-
August, according to an interview with La Republica.  Pacific Rubiales (PREC CB), the Toronto-based oil producer
that operates fields in Colombia, rose 0.3 percent to 48,140
pesos. The company bucked falling oil prices and advanced for
the first time in four sessions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
